Rider Tips

üîÅ
Out & Back or Shuttle
Full 19 miles is typically done as out-and-back (38 mi) or with a car shuttle at each end. Many riders do 10‚Äì12 mi from Seaside.
‚ö°
E-Bikes Recommended
Several shops rent e-bikes on 30A, making the full trail very comfortable for casual riders and families of any fitness level.
üö¶
Road Crossings
The trail crosses 30A many times. Slow at every intersection ‚Äî some lack signals. Watch for driveways too.
üåâ
Draper Lake Covered Bridge
Don't miss the covered bridge near mile 4.5 ‚Äî one of the most peaceful and photogenic moments on the entire trail.
üç¶
Best Stop: Seaside
Mile ~10. Airstream food trucks, rooftop bars, beach. The Truman Show was filmed here. Perfect halfway turnaround point.
üåÖ
Best Time to Ride
Early morning for cool temps and thin crowds. Avoid peak summer afternoons. Busiest near Seaside and Rosemary Beach.
üíß
Water & Restrooms
Beach access points along the route have water and restrooms. Stock up at Grayton SP or Seaside before remote stretches.
üåä
Coastal Dune Lakes
15 globally rare coastal dune lakes line this trail. Western Lake at mile 7.5 is the largest ‚Äî occasionally breaks through to the Gulf!
